This paper discusses a new multi-agent based Cloud Resource Bartering System (CRBS) that fosters the management and bartering of pooled resources without requiring costly financial transactions between IAAS cloud providers. The paper focuses on the management of cloud resources and the use of multi-agent systems, which are typically covered in the Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) category. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of AI techniques to assign resources based on urgency, which falls under the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) category. The paper also discusses the use of inter-cloud resource sharing systems, which are covered in the Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) category. The paper also discusses the use of networking technologies to facilitate resource sharing, which falls under the Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) category. Finally, the paper discusses the economic benefits of the proposed system, which falls under the Computational Economics and Finance (cs.CE) category.
